translated: Åstrand, Otto Arvid, licentiate of theology, bachelor of philosophy, pastor, Oskarshamn, b. 11/12/82 in Näshult, Jönköping County, son of Joh. Aug. A. and Helena Andersdotter. Married on 13' to Elsa Bohman. Children: Maj-Britte b. 14, Ingrid b. 16, Birgit b. 22. - Passed student's exam in 1907, bachelor of philosophy in 1910, licentiate of theology in 1913, practical theology exam in 1913, ordained as a priest in 1913, licentiate of theology in 1938. Curate in Stenberga from 1916, in Hakarp from 1918, parish priest in Hälleberga from 1920, in Oskarshamn since 1932. Inspector for secondary school since 1938. Chairman of church council and church assembly, member of diaconate board from 1918-1931, member of mission board from 1920-1932, member of Växjö diocese council from 1922-1932. Inspector for Orrefors vocational school from 1929-1932, lecturer association Gulla-skruv from 1929-1932, lecturer association Oskarshamn since 1935. Member of the twelve-man board for Sweden's Christian War Veterans Association in Uppsala from 1936-1943, chairman of SvRK Oskarshamn branch from 1937-1942, chairman of the board for Oskarshamn elementary school (and others) from 1934-1935, member of the central board for Swedish cremation association since 1941. Awarded Order of Vasa in 1944.
